uC++ Syntax Highlighting for Vim

To install:

1. Copy ucpp.vim into ~/.vim/syntax/
2. Add the following lines into your .vimrc
  au BufRead,BufNewFile *.ucpp set filetype=ucpp
  au BufRead,BufNewFile *.uh set filetype=ucpp

Now any file with the extension '.ucpp' or '.uh' will be highlighted for uC++
keywords or predefined objects. Alternatively, you can modify the code above to
recognize any filetype you decide.
